Help Type: topic
Topic: readiness

Readiness

Purpose:
  Use this when `inspect` reports missing `--query` support, generated data, or provider configuration.
  Readiness explains what must exist before `--query`, Reading Graph, summaries, and Knowledge Graph retrieval can work.

Start with inspect:
  wikigraph <archive-uri> inspect

FTS readiness:
  `--query` uses the archive FTS index. Without a current index, keyword retrieval is unavailable for scopes, evidence, and related results.

  Default behavior:
    The FTS index is built as local cache outside the `.wikg` archive.
    This keeps the archive smaller, but the index does not travel with copied archive files.
    If another user receives the `.wikg`, they usually need to build their own local index.

  Portable behavior:
    You can embed the built index into the `.wikg` archive.
    This makes the archive more self-contained, but increases file size.
    If you are unsure, build the local index first and embed only when distribution convenience matters.

  Commands:
    wikigraph <archive-uri>/index
    wikigraph <archive-uri>/index build --help
    wikigraph <archive-uri>/index embed --help
    wikigraph <archive-uri>/index external --help

Generation readiness:
  Reading Graph, Reading Summary, and Knowledge Graph data are generated artifacts.
  They do not appear just because source text exists.

  All generation jobs require LLM configuration:
    wikigraph wikg://local/config/llm
    wikigraph wikg://local/config/llm test

  Inspect job commands before starting expensive work:
    wikigraph wikg://local/job --help
    wikigraph wikg://local/job add --help

LLM readiness:
  `wikg://local/config/llm` is required for generating:
  - Reading Graph
  - Reading Summary
  - Knowledge Graph

  Minimum configuration:
    provider
    model
    provider credentials when required

  Common path:
    wikigraph wikg://local/config/llm put provider openai
    wikigraph wikg://local/config/llm put model gpt-4.1
    wikigraph wikg://local/config/llm put apiKey --secret
    wikigraph wikg://local/config/llm test

WikiSpine readiness:
  Knowledge Graph generation also requires WikiSpine.
  WikiSpine provides entity candidate lookup for Knowledge Graph construction.

  Provider choices:
  - `fetch`: use an HTTP endpoint. This is usually easier for Agents and hosted setups when a service URL is available.
  - `cli`: run a local `wikispine` command. This is useful for offline or locally controlled environments, but requires local runtime setup and data.

  Configure one provider, then test it:
    wikigraph wikg://local/config/wikispine put provider fetch
    wikigraph wikg://local/config/wikispine put endpoint https://example.com
    wikigraph wikg://local/config/wikispine test

    wikigraph wikg://local/config/wikispine put provider cli
    wikigraph wikg://local/config/wikispine put command wikispine
    wikigraph wikg://local/config/wikispine test

How to choose:
  - Need keyword retrieval on this machine: build local index.
  - Need to send a more self-contained `.wikg`: consider embedding the index after it is built.
  - Need generated Reading Graph or summaries: configure LLM and use local jobs.
  - Need Knowledge Graph: configure LLM and WikiSpine, then use local jobs.
  - Not sure whether to embed index or generate missing data: keep the archive external/local first, inspect again, and decide later.

